{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/paperfaces/miriamchadwick-portrait/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Curly hair in a knit hat","date":"2013-07-15T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"July 15th, 2013","date_from_now":"7 years ago","last_modified_at":null,"last_modified_at_from_now":null,"path":"/paperfaces/miriamchadwick-portrait/","author":null,"excerpt":"PaperFaces portrait of @miriamchadwick drawn with Paper for iOS on an iPad.","tags":["portrait","illustration","Paper for iOS"],"image":null,"toc":null,"comments":null,"comments_locked":null,"hide_meta":null},"id":"bc83aed1-85f9-5ffc-9dce-98891a63e0bd","html":"<p>PaperFaces portrait of <a href=\"http://instagram.com/miriamchadwick\">@miriamchadwick</a>.</p>\n<p>99.9% of the time I start with the background first.</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../images/paperfaces-miriamchadwick-process-1-lg.jpg\" alt=\"Work in process screenshot\"></p>\n<p>Build up the figure with pencil first, watercolor second, and back to pencil for refinements.</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../images/paperfaces-miriamchadwick-process-2-lg.jpg\" alt=\"Work in process screenshot\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"../../images/paperfaces-miriamchadwick-process-3-lg.jpg\" alt=\"Work in process screenshot\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"../../images/paperfaces-miriamchadwick-process-4-lg.jpg\" alt=\"Work in process screenshot\"></p>\n<p>Using a pencil to add detail gradually. Using a Pogo Connect pen that supports pressure sensitivity makes this much easier.</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../images/paperfaces-miriamchadwick-process-5-lg.jpg\" alt=\"Work in process screenshot\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"../../images/paperfaces-miriamchadwick-process-6-lg.jpg\" alt=\"Work in process screenshot\"></p>\n<p>Rendering hair in Paper can be a lot of fun if you take your time. Start dark and gradually mix white or yellow into the color mixer to make strands that are highlighted.</p>\n<p><img src=\"../../images/paperfaces-miriamchadwick-process-7-lg.jpg\" alt=\"Work in process screenshot\"></p>\n<p><strong>Tools used:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B009K448L4/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&#x26;camp=1789&#x26;creative=390957&#x26;creativeASIN=B009K448L4&#x26;linkCode=as2&#x26;tag=mademist-20\">Pogo Connect Bluetooth Smart Pen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://paper.bywetransfer.com/\">Paper for iOS</a></li>\n</ul>","excerpt":"PaperFaces portrait of @miriamchadwick. 99.9% of the time I start with the background first. Work in process screenshot Build up the figureâ€¦","timeToRead":1,"tableOfContents":""},"comments":{"edges":[]}},"pageContext":{"next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/paperfaces/leviwintering-portrait/","title":"A full face in low contrast","categories":["paperfaces"],"tags":["portrait","illustration","Paper for iOS","black and white"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/balajin/Workspace/made-mistakes-gatsby/src/posts/paperfaces/leviwintering-portrait.md"},"previous":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/paperfaces/andispringer-portrait/","title":"Dramatic contrast and a hint of smile","categories":["paperfaces"],"tags":["portrait","illustration","Paper for iOS","black and white"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/balajin/Workspace/made-mistakes-gatsby/src/posts/paperfaces/andispringer-portrait.md"}}}}